cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "The Unsolved Mathematics Atlas"
message: "If you use this atlas or its meta-analyses, please cite it as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: "Donahue"
    given-names: "Alexander"
    alias: "0thernes"
    email: "0_0@0thernes.art"
    # orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0000-0000-0000"  # add your ORCID if you have one
repository-code: "https://github.com/0thernes/unsolved-mathematics"
url: "https://github.com/0thernes/unsolved-mathematics"
abstract: >
  An exhaustive, ranked, research-grade dossier collection of humanity's open
  mathematical problems (106 problems across 38 fields). Each problem includes
  its history, originator biography, attack strategies, notable attempts, 25 key
  papers, 10 key mathematicians, and a retrieval-augmented knowledge corpus.
  Problems are ranked by a transparent, reproducible Composite Severity Score.
  Accompanying AI-assisted meta-analyses are curated by the human-in-the-loop
  author and undergo a multi-model AI review panel (Grok, Gemini, GPT, Claude)
  prior to human academic verification.
keywords:
  - mathematics
  - open problems
  - conjectures
  - meta-analysis
  - AI-assisted research
  - retrieval-augmented generation
  - knowledge base
